      fix(dart): bump tree-sitter-dart to upstream master (02e9bb19) (#590)
      
      * fix(dart): bump tree-sitter-dart to upstream master (02e9bb19)
      
      Brings in 13 upstream commits since the May 2023 pin (80e23c07): the
      parser-improvements PR (#97), the Dart 3.10 dot-shorthand support
      (#93), get/set contextual keyword fixes (#89, #92), the
      extension-type-declarations support (#83), the CI/tree-sitter 0.25
      compatibility fixes, and the recently-merged record-return + leading
      annotation fix (#98).
      
      * fix(semgrep-dart): hide `semgrep_pattern` choice rule
      
      The wrapper grammar declared `semgrep_pattern` as a public rule:
      
        semgrep_pattern: $ => choice($._expression, $._statement),
      
      so tree-sitter emitted a `(semgrep_pattern …)` node in the parse tree.
      Two corpus tests in `test/corpus/semgrep.txt` (`Standalone expression`
      and `Standalone metavariable ellipsis`) wrote their expected output
      without that wrapper, so they failed. The wrapper node carries no
      semantic information — it's just a choice point between two
      alternatives.
      
      Rename to `_semgrep_pattern` (leading underscore = tree-sitter's
      hidden-rule convention). The parse tree now inlines the choice's
      result directly under `semgrep_expression`, the corpus tests pass as
      written, and `ocaml-tree-sitter simplify` un-hides the rule before
      generating the OCaml CST so the downstream artifact (and the OCaml
      mapper) is unaffected.
      
      Verified: `cd lang/semgrep-grammars/src/semgrep-dart && tree-sitter
      test` — 6/6 pass (was 4/6). Also re-ran the full
      `lang/dart` artifact build: regenerated `parser.c`, `Boilerplate.ml`,
      `CST.ml`, `Parse.ml` are byte-identical to the pre-change versions
      (simplification re-introduces the rule for OCaml processing), so no
      downstream artifact change is needed.
